flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Daily scheduled planning run or demand signal change (forecast update or large confirmed order) from SAP S/4HANA / Cortex Auto Forecast.]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Ingest master data, orders, cost rates, and historical production/downtime into subject areas]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex Auto Forecast - Generate/upsert demand forecasts and scenario demand signals]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Process (Process Builder) + Remote Functions - Run network capacity simulation and bottleneck detection]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process (Process Builder) - Rules / IF - Apply business rules to select final allocation and sequencing}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions + Process (Process Builder) - Action Item / Notification - Execute plan: write schedules to SAP and create operator action items and dashboards]
  N5 --> N6[UI: UI Screen / Subject Areas / Dashboard - Surface plan, KPIs and bottleneck mitigation tasks for review]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Network-level production plan that reduces bottleneck impact, improves line throughput, lowers unit COGS through optimized allocation and sequencing, and better aligns capacity to demand with automated execution and clear operator tasks.]
  N4 -->|Network demand exceeds aggregate avai...| B1[Invoke constrained optimization routine (Remote Functions) with prioritized objectives (margin, customer SL) and produce prioritized allocation + recommended trade-offs (overtime, subcontracting, order reschedule).]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Feasible, prioritized production plan with clear service-level tradeoffs and actionable recommendations for capacity augmentation or order adjustments.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Critical bottleneck detected with no ...| B2[Create Action Item and Notification to operations and planning team; suggest temporary measures (overtime, line re-sequencing, part reroute) and open CWB Lifecycle exception for manual approval.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Human-in-the-loop intervention to resolve the bottleneck; plan paused or adjusted pending remediation, preserving safety and policy compliance.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Incomplete or low-quality data from S...| B3[Process Builder raises data-quality exception, routes to exception queue (CWB Lifecycle) and halts finalization until required data is corrected or a planner overrides with documented assumptions.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Prevent incorrect allocations; ensure manual remediation or documented override before schedule writeback.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]